{{2016 ACC football standings}}
The '''2016 Atlantic Coast Conference football season''' was the 64th season of [[college football]] play for the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC), played from September 2016 to January 2017. The [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] consists of 14 members in two divisions. The Atlantic Division consists of [[2016 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]], [[2016 Clemson Tigers football team|Clemson]], [[2016 Florida State Seminoles football team|Florida State]], [[2016 Louisville Cardinals football team|Louisville]], [[2016 NC State Wolfpack football team|North Carolina State]], [[2016 Syracuse Orange football team|Syracuse]], and [[2016 Wake Forest Demon Deacons football team|Wake Forest]]. The Coastal Division consists of [[2016 Duke Blue Devils football team|Duke]], [[2016 Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football team|Georgia Tech]], [[2016 Miami Hurricanes football team|Miami]], [[2016 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]], [[2016 Pittsburgh Panthers football team|Pittsburgh]], [[2016 Virginia Cavaliers football team|Virginia]], and [[2016 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|Virginia Tech]]. The two division champions met on December 3 in the [[2016 ACC Championship Game]]. The game was originally scheduled to be played at [[Bank of America Stadium]] in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]], but on September 14 the conference announced that the game would be moved to a neutral venue outside of [[North Carolina]] due to the controversy surrounding the [[Public Facilities Privacy & Security Act]] (commonly known as House Bill 2, or HB2).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/college-football/news/acc-to-relocate-2016-football-championship-from-north-carolina-due-to-hb2-law/|title=ACC to relocate 2016 football championship from North Carolina due to HB2 law|date=September 14, 2016|author=Chip Patterson|publisher=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref>

==Preseason==
===Preseason Poll===
The 2016 ACC Preseason Poll was announced following the ACC Football Kickoff meetings in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]] on July 21–22.<ref>{{cite web|title=ACC Announces Student-Athletes Attending the 2016 ACC Football Kickoff|url=http://www.theacc.com/news/student-athletes-attending-acc-football-kickoff-07-11-2016|publisher=TheACC.com|access-date=25 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714082601/http://www.theacc.com/news/student-athletes-attending-acc-football-kickoff-07-11-2016|archive-date=14 July 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> North Carolina and Clemson were each selected to repeat in their respective divisions. Deshaun Watson of Clemson was once again voted the Preseason ACC Player of the Year.<ref>
{{cite web| year=2016| title=Clemson Leads ACC Football Kickoff Preseason Poll| publisher=Atlantic Coast Conference| url=http://www.theacc.com/news/clemson-leads-acc-football-kickoff-preseason-poll-07-25-2016| access-date=25 July 2016| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727193504/http://www.theacc.com/news/clemson-leads-acc-football-kickoff-preseason-poll-07-25-2016| archive-date=27 July 2016| url-status=dead| df=dmy-all}}
</ref>  It was voted on by 191 media members, all of which were in attendance for the ACC Football Kickoff.

